creator: William Makepeace Thackeray
description:
LibriVox recording of The Rose And The Ring by William Makepeace Thackeray.
Read in English by Eleanor Howard; Domenica Campbell; Cancer; Lydia; Lynne Thompson
Victorian social satire hiding in a set of children's fairy tales by the author of the classic "Vanity Fair" - Summary by Stav Nisser
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: librivox; audiobooks;satire; children; fantasy; short stories; fairy tales; victorian
